svg.title: Present weather reported from a manned weather station: Precipitation within sight, reaching the ground or the surface of the sea, but distant, i.e. estimated to be more than 5 km from the station
svg.desc: WMO international weather symbol: No precipitation at the station at the time of observation: No precipitation, fog, ice fog, duststorm, sandstorm, drifting or blowing snow at the station* at the time of observation or during the preceding hour. *The expression “at the station” refers to a land station or a ship: Present weather reported from a manned weather station: Precipitation within sight, reaching the ground or the surface of the sea, but distant, i.e. estimated to be more than 5 km from the station
